"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-rowing-2024-0521-1450405-womens-four-olympic-bound-but-heartbreak-for-puspure\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Eoin Ryan  RT\\u00c9 Sport Journalist  The Irish women's four will again fight for an Olympic medal after securing a place in Paris at the final qualification regatta.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 9, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_Ryan_Jnr\", \"score\": 0.9958233276122709, \"rank\": 0.00419419014589494, \"text\": \"Eoin Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_Ryan_Jnr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_Ryan_Jnr\"}, {\"begin\": 120, \"end\": 125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995684348527, \"rank\": 4.3156539753560045e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emily Hegarty, Natalie Long, Eimear Lambe and Imogen Magnerneeded to finish in the top two of the A final to book their Olympic spot and while that rarely looked in doubt they did it in style, pipping Denmark by just .79 of a second after a neck-and-neck battle over the final 1500m.Lambe and Hegarty won bronze in the event in Tokyo with Fiona Murtagh and Aifric Keogh, who secured a place this time as the women's pair, one of an Olympic record seven boats qualified for Ireland, one more than in 2021.\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Hegarty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emily Hegarty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Hegarty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Hegarty\"}, {\"begin\": 364, \"end\": 371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.986721557390889, \"rank\": 0.013411963863253428, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999857262259945, \"rank\": 1.4241210903919184e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Murtagh\", \"score\": 0.999998793390478, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fiona Murtagh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Murtagh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Murtagh\"}, {\"begin\": 520, \"end\": 532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aifric_Keogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aifric Keogh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aifric_Keogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aifric_Keogh\"}, {\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999995347299037, \"rank\": 4.651307657237501e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However,Sanita Puspuremissed out on a fourth consecutive Olympic appearance after misfortune struck and she finished fifth in the women's single sculls A final.\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 42-year-old Cork-based rower went out hard and led Spain's Virginia Diaz Rivas, who had also won her heat and semi-final, by over three seconds at the halfway stage, having covered the opening 1000m in 03:50.70.\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999667199978, \"rank\": 3.087229187435556e-08, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former World and European champion Puspure was still almost two seconds ahead with 500m to go but then appeared to hit a buoy and briefly stop rowing, eventually finishing in 08:03.05 as Rivas (07:48.16) and home favourite Aurelia-Maxima Katharina Janzen (07:49.85) took first and second.\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9963397852831167, \"rank\": 0.0025479324349638455, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 1235, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rivas_Department\", \"score\": 0.9961782377671912, \"rank\": 0.0034250555211283186, \"text\": \"Rivas\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rivas_Department\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rivas_Department\"}, {\"begin\": 1296, \"end\": 1302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_H._Janzen\", \"score\": 0.9999990307114935, \"rank\": 9.294358896892745e-07, \"text\": \"Janzen\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_H._Janzen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_H._Janzen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Konan Pazzaiawas sixth in the men's single sculls A final.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Third in his semi-final yesterday, the 22-year-old made a fast start in his native country, hitting the front after 500m and was second at the halfway mark, just behind eventual winner Mihai Chiruta of Romania.\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Pazzaia, whose mother is from Belfast, was being reeled in by the field as the race progressed and finished in 07:08.81, just over nine seconds behind Chiruta.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1649, \"end\": 1656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belfast\", \"score\": 0.9999996617880814, \"rank\": 3.038571675814003e-07, \"text\": \"Belfast\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belfast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belfast\"}, {\"begin\": 1770, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chirutha\", \"score\": 0.9999999366202721, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chiruta\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chirutha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chirutha\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851268295, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 1842, \"end\": 1849, \"title\": \"http://dbpe